  340. ‌let stable_sort cmp l =
  341.   let rec rev_merge l1 l2 accu =
  342.     match l1, l2 with
  343.     | [], l2 -> rev_append l2 accu
  344.     | l1, [] -> rev_append l1 accu
  345.     | h1::t1, h2::t2 ->
  346.         if cmp h1 h2 <= 0
  347.         then rev_merge t1 l2 (h1::accu)
  348.         else rev_merge l1 t2 (h2::accu)

  350.   let rec rev_merge_rev l1 l2 accu =
  351.     match l1, l2 with
  352.     | [], l2 -> rev_append l2 accu
  353.     | l1, [] -> rev_append l1 accu
  354.     | h1::t1, h2::t2 ->
  355.         if cmp h1 h2 > 0
  356.         then rev_merge_rev t1 l2 (h1::accu)
  357.         else rev_merge_rev l1 t2 (h2::accu)
  358.   in
  359.   let rec sort n l =
  360.     match n, l with
  361.     | 2, x1 :: x2 :: tl ->
  362.         let s = if cmp x1 x2 <= 0 then [x1; x2] else [x2; x1] in
  363.         (s, tl)
  364.     | 3, x1 :: x2 :: x3 :: tl ->
  365. ‌        let s =
  366.           if cmp x1 x2 <= 0 then
  367.             if cmp x2 x3 <= 0 then [x1; x2; x3]
  368.             else if cmp x1 x3 <= 0 then [x1; x3; x2]
  369.             else [x3; x1; x2]
  370.           else if cmp x1 x3 <= 0 then [x2; x1; x3]
  371.           else if cmp x2 x3 <= 0 then [x2; x3; x1]
  372.           else [x3; x2; x1]
  373.         in
  374.         (s, tl)
  375.     | n, l ->
  376. ‌        let n1 = n asr 1 in
  377. ‌        let n2 = n - n1 in
  378. ‌        let s1, l2 = rev_sort n1 l in
  379. ‌        let s2, tl = rev_sort n2 l2 in
  380.         (rev_merge_rev s1 s2 [], tl)
  381. ‌  and rev_sort n l =

  389.             if cmp x2 x3 > 0 then [x1; x2; x3]
  390.             else if cmp x1 x3 > 0 then [x1; x3; x2]
  391.             else [x3; x1; x2]
  392.           else if cmp x1 x3 > 0 then [x2; x1; x3]
  393.           else if cmp x2 x3 > 0 then [x2; x3; x1]
  394.           else [x3; x2; x1]

  419. ‌let sort_uniq cmp l =
  420.   let rec rev_merge l1 l2 accu =
  421.     match l1, l2 with
  422.     | [], l2 -> rev_append l2 accu
  423.     | l1, [] -> rev_append l1 accu
  424.     | h1::t1, h2::t2 ->
  425.         let c = cmp h1 h2 in
  426.         if c = 0 then rev_merge t1 t2 (h1::accu)
  427.         else if c < 0
  428.         then rev_merge t1 l2 (h1::accu)
  429.         else rev_merge l1 t2 (h2::accu)
  430.   in
  431.   let rec rev_merge_rev l1 l2 accu =
  432.     match l1, l2 with
  433.     | [], l2 -> rev_append l2 accu
  434.     | l1, [] -> rev_append l1 accu
  435.     | h1::t1, h2::t2 ->
  436.         let c = cmp h1 h2 in
  437.         if c = 0 then rev_merge_rev t1 t2 (h1::accu)
  438.         else if c > 0
  439.         then rev_merge_rev t1 l2 (h1::accu)
  440.         else rev_merge_rev l1 t2 (h2::accu)
  441.   in
  442.   let rec sort n l =
  443.     match n, l with
  444.     | 2, x1 :: x2 :: tl ->
  445.         let s =
  446.           let c = cmp x1 x2 in
  447.           if c = 0 then [x1] else if c < 0 then [x1; x2] else [x2; x1]
  448.         in
  449.         (s, tl)
  450.     | 3, x1 :: x2 :: x3 :: tl ->
  451. ‌        let s =
  452.           let c = cmp x1 x2 in
  453.           if c = 0 then
  454.             let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  455.             if c = 0 then [x2] else if c < 0 then [x2; x3] else [x3; x2]
  456.           else if c < 0 then
  457.             let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  458.             if c = 0 then [x1; x2]
  459.             else if c < 0 then [x1; x2; x3]
  460.             else
  461.               let c = cmp x1 x3 in
  462.               if c = 0 then [x1; x2]
  463.               else if c < 0 then [x1; x3; x2]
  464.               else [x3; x1; x2]
  465.           else
  466.             let c = cmp x1 x3 in
  467.             if c = 0 then [x2; x1]
  468.             else if c < 0 then [x2; x1; x3]
  469.             else
  470.               let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  471.               if c = 0 then [x2; x1]
  472.               else if c < 0 then [x2; x3; x1]
  473.               else [x3; x2; x1]
  474.         in
  475.         (s, tl)
  476.     | n, l ->
  477. ‌        let n1 = n asr 1 in
  478. ‌        let n2 = n - n1 in
  479. ‌        let s1, l2 = rev_sort n1 l in
  480. ‌        let s2, tl = rev_sort n2 l2 in
  481.         (rev_merge_rev s1 s2 [], tl)
  482. ‌  and rev_sort n l =
  483.     match n, l with
  484.     | 2, x1 :: x2 :: tl ->
  485.         let s =
  486.           let c = cmp x1 x2 in
  487.           if c = 0 then [x1] else if c > 0 then [x1; x2] else [x2; x1]
  488.         in
  489.         (s, tl)
  490.     | 3, x1 :: x2 :: x3 :: tl ->
  491. ‌        let s =
  492.           let c = cmp x1 x2 in
  493.           if c = 0 then
  494.             let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  495.             if c = 0 then [x2] else if c > 0 then [x2; x3] else [x3; x2]
  496.           else if c > 0 then
  497.             let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  498.             if c = 0 then [x1; x2]
  499.             else if c > 0 then [x1; x2; x3]
  500.             else
  501.               let c = cmp x1 x3 in
  502.               if c = 0 then [x1; x2]
  503.               else if c > 0 then [x1; x3; x2]
  504.               else [x3; x1; x2]
  505.           else
  506.             let c = cmp x1 x3 in
  507.             if c = 0 then [x2; x1]
  508.             else if c > 0 then [x2; x1; x3]
  509.             else
  510.               let c = cmp x2 x3 in
  511.               if c = 0 then [x2; x1]
  512.               else if c > 0 then [x2; x3; x1]
  513.               else [x3; x2; x1]
  514.         in
  515.         (s, tl)
  516.     | n, l ->
  517. ‌        let n1 = n asr 1 in
  518. ‌        let n2 = n - n1 in
  519. ‌        let s1, l2 = sort n1 l in
  520. ‌        let s2, tl = sort n2 l2 in
  521.         (rev_merge s1 s2 [], tl)
  522.   in
  523. ‌  let len = length l in
  524.   if len < 2 then l else fst (sort len l)


  527. ‌let rec compare_lengths l1 l2 =
  528.   match l1, l2 with
  529.   | [], [] -> 0
  530.   | [], _ -> -1
  531.   | _, [] -> 1
  532.   | _ :: l1, _ :: l2 -> compare_lengths l1 l2

  534. ‌let rec compare_length_with l n =
  535.   match l with
  536.   | [] ->
  537.     if n = 0 then 0 else
  538.       if n > 0 then -1 else 1
  539.   | _ :: l ->
  540.     if n <= 0 then 1 else
  541.       compare_length_with l (n-1)

  543. ‌let is_empty = function
  544.   | [] -> true
  545.   | _ :: _ -> false

  547. (** {1 Comparison} *)

  549. (* Note: we are *not* shortcutting the list by using
  550.    [List.compare_lengths] first; this may be slower on long lists
  551.    immediately start with distinct elements. It is also incorrect for
  552.    [compare] below, and it is better (principle of least surprise) to
  553.    use the same approach for both functions. *)
  554. ‌let rec equal eq l1 l2 =
  555.   match l1, l2 with
  556.   | [], [] -> true
  557.   | [], _::_ | _::_, [] -> false
  558.   | a1::l1, a2::l2 -> eq a1 a2 && equal eq l1 l2

  560. ‌let rec compare cmp l1 l2 =
  561.   match l1, l2 with
  562.   | [], [] -> 0
  563.   | [], _::_ -> -1
  564.   | _::_, [] -> 1
  565.   | a1::l1, a2::l2 ->
  566.     let c = cmp a1 a2 in
  567.     if c <> 0 then c
  568.     else compare cmp l1 l2

  570. (** {1 Iterators} *)

  572. ‌let to_seq l =
  573.   let rec aux l () = match l with
  574.     | [] -> Seq.Nil
  575.     | x :: tail -> Seq.Cons (x, aux tail)
  576.   in
  577.   aux l

  579. let[@tail_mod_cons] rec of_seq seq =
  580.   match seq () with
  581.   | Seq.Nil -> []
  582.   | Seq.Cons (x1, seq) ->
  583.       begin match seq () with
  584.       | Seq.Nil -> [x1]
  585.       | Seq.Cons (x2, seq) -> x1 :: x2 :: of_seq seq
  586.       end
